Swiss Equity Preview: Credit Suisse Group, Swatch Group May Move

-- B y   S i m o n e   M e i e r
-- 
2011-06-06T04:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-05/swiss-equity-preview-credit-suisse-group-swatch-group-may-move.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in Zurich. Stock
symbols are in parentheses after company names. Share prices are
from the last close.  The  Swiss Market Index (SMI)  of the biggest and most actively
traded companies slipped 1.4 percent to 6,407.39. The broader
Swiss Performance Index fell 1.3 percent to 5,902.92.  Credit Suisse Group AG (CSGN)  : Switzerland’s second-
largest bank plans to make an offer to some private customers
holding structured investment products issued by Lehman Brothers
Holdings Inc., Tages-Anzeiger reported. The bank plans to pool
the assets and offer them for sale to investors such as  hedge
funds , the newspaper said. Credit Suisse fell 1.4 percent to
35.81 francs.  Swatch Group AG (UHR)  : Swatch Chief Executive Officer
Nick Hayek said the watchmaker is losing 50 million Swiss francs
($60 million) to 60 million francs in revenue every month
because of the Swiss currency’s ascent, SonntagsZeitung
reported, citing an interview. Swatch shares fell 1.9 percent to
414 francs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Simone Meier in Zurich at 
 smeier@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
